cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.NE

This paper is about stance detection in fake news, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, such as neural networks and ensemble learning, which are commonly used in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper deals with finding relevant information sources. Finally, the use of word embeddings and neural networks suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
